Steve Brinich (steve-b@access.digex.net) writes:

>   DOS PGP users should probably stick to 2.2, or 2.1 if the incompatibility
> between 2.2 and some types of compression rears its ugly head in their
> systems.

DOS PGP users should -particularly- avoid version 2.2. It contains a
bug which may cause your hard disk to be trashed. If you -have- to use
version 2.2, be sure to turn the compression off.

